			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Join the GOOD/Corps Strategy Team as one of its Directors!</strong></p>
<p>
<a href="http://www.goodcorps.com">GOOD/Corps</a>, GOOD&rsquo;s social innovation consultancy, is searching for a <strong>Strategy</strong>&nbsp;<strong>Director </strong>to join our Los Angeles office. We partner with leading brands, foundations and nonprofits to surface and manifest world-changing shared value opportunities. Our work ranges from launching new businesses to sparking highly participatory social programs.</p>
<p>
As a Director, you&rsquo;ll leverage your world-class expertise and social impact savvy to oversee the creation of breakthrough client strategies, the health and growth of our partnerships, and the profitable delivery of work. You&rsquo;ll be an active speaker/writer/contributor in the social impact space and will deftly represent the work and potential of GOOD/Corps to prospective partners. You&rsquo;ll lead client engagements from beginning to end and, as a member of the GOOD/Corps Senior Team, will have an active hand in shaping our ongoing business and impact strategy.</p>
<p>
<strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Internalize client challenges at the business development stage and beyond, identify and frame the critical variables at play, and paint/own a clear and compelling picture of success for both the project and long-term client relationship</li>
<li>
Lead project scoping, pricing, and resourcing, setting clear and achievable expectations with client and team</li>
<li>
Develop and manage a team workplan to ensure strategic output that addresses client challenges and adheres to GOOD/Corps&rsquo; world-class standards</li>
<li>
Provide operational leadership to the project team to ensure on-time execution of key deliverables, balancing the fulfillment of project goals with the professional growth and satisfaction of individuals</li>
<li>
Manage and report on project P&amp;L, client satisfaction, and content</li>
<li>
Effectively manage the formal and informal professional development of team members through skill planning, coaching, and performance feedback</li>
<li>
Develop advisory relationships with clients, as well as other sector leaders, that extends beyond the bounds of a project</li>
<li>
Proactively identify opportunities to serve as an external beacon for the work we do, the methodologies we employ, and the shared values space overall (speaking engagements, blogging, etc.)</li>
<li>
Serve in various ad-hoc leadership capacities</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Essential Attributes</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Strategic: </strong>Draws sharp insights and turns them into tangible recommendations</li>
<li>
<strong>Creative: </strong>Consistently generates new ideas and connections to create solutions beyond what exists today</li>
<li>
<strong>Social Impact Driven: </strong>Champions a shared value philosophy to project results</li>
<li>
<strong>Entrepreneurial:</strong> Drives new ideas and work forward</li>
<li>
<strong>Organized / Detail-Oriented: </strong>Brings the highest order of attentiveness to all work</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements/Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree required; Master&rsquo;s degree preferred</li>
<li>
8-12 years of client services, management consulting, social impact consulting, design thinking agency and/or other relevant work experience</li>
<li>
Demonstrated commitment to and/or work in the social impact space</li>
<li>
Deep expertise in 1-2 relevant areas (social impact, HCD, business strategy, etc.)</li>
<li>
Demonstrated experience creating actionable strategies that fuse creativity and rigor, building and managing teams, and forging trusted relationships with clients</li>
<li>
Flexibility to meet shifting client needs and priorities</li>
<li>
Strong organizational and people management skills</li>
<li>
Strong interpersonal skills;&nbsp;open, friendly and supportive attitude</li>
<li>
The desire to do excellent work and have fun doing it</li>
<li>
The drive and commitment to help GOOD/Corps grow successfully</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Bonus if you have...</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Global sensibility. You watch Al Jazeera, understand the parliamentary system, hablas espa&ntilde;ol. Even better if you have international expertise and/or work experience abroad.</li>
<li>
Passion outside of work. Our team consists of mathematicians, chefs, entrepreneurs, and social innovators, and we thrive off the energy that&rsquo;s created when diverse minds come together. What will you bring?</li>
</ul>
