			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>About GOOD</strong></p>
<p>
GOOD is a global community of people who give a damn.&nbsp; Our new platform is a gathering place and a growing toolkit for pragmatic idealists to creatively and collaboratively engage with each other, our communities, and our world. We help you connect with awesome people and organizations, and engage with them around topics and issues you care about.</p>
<p>
<strong>GOOD Campus Ambassador Program</strong></p>
<p>
At universities around the country, there are many students and groups trying to push the world forward through their separate initiatives. However, we at GOOD believe that more impact can be made when people come together.</p>
<p>
GOOD&rsquo;s Campus Ambassadors are charged with convening and organizing student innovators to collaborate and collectively drive change. As a GOOD Campus Ambassador, you will bring the creativity, energy and drive of your university&rsquo;s students to the GOOD community and work with GOOD HQ to maximize your collective impact. As part of our pilot program, each student ambassador will have a hand in shaping this program.</p>
<p>
<strong>Location:</strong>&nbsp; On your university campus</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Build and manage your university&rsquo;s hub on good.is, making it the go-to place for info on social good content and action opportunities that are relevant for your campus</li>
<li>
Each semester, execute one major creative initiative (e.g., event, exhibit, campaign), with guidance from GOOD HQ and our partners (leading social impact organizations)</li>
<li>
Network and collaborate with student organizations and professors, including building a coalition of like-minded student groups and managing regular meet-ups</li>
<li>
Share ideas and best practices with other GOOD Campus Ambassadors across the country</li>
<li>
This is an opportunity to build professional skills in project management, communications, and community organizing.&nbsp; You&rsquo;ll gain first-hand experience working at a successful social enterprise and be able to network with influencers in the fields of media, technology, design, business, and social impact.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Background / skills:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Strong communications and problem solving skills</li>
<li>
A go-getter attitude and a willingness to try new things</li>
<li>
Active on campus and enjoys collaborating with peers</li>
<li>
Ability to rally a community and get people excited</li>
<li>
Creative and has the ability to think outside the box</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
